{
  "stem": "9701.3",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But that one section of France, which was referred to as Vichy, France, sort of seceded from the rest of France and collaborated with the Nazis.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And that's where Camp De Gurs and several other camps were located.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "It was perhaps an aberration of the war, but my parents were able to communicate directly with me once they were in Camp De Gurs.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "It went through the censorship.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And they were limited as to how often and how much they could write.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Men and women were separate in Camp De Gurs, separated by barbed wire.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "I understand that in the beginning, once a month, men and women were allowed to spend one hour together.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "In fact--",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I learned that afterwards.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Again, my parents didn't share that with me.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But I have in my possession a photograph, a family photograph that was taken in Gurs.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It had to be taken fairly early.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I don't know who took it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I don't know how it got out.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And it shows men and women, my family, together.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And it had to be taken fairly early, because they look, still, quite well.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "When I was in the Holocaust Museum in Washington DC, I saw some photographs in their archives of people taken later on in the camp, and they looked like mere skeletons.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So, that's why I'm thinking it was taken early.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "My grandfather, my mother's father, is not on that photograph.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I know that he died two months after he arrived there.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Now, whether he was still alive, or maybe he was too sick to be on that photograph, I don't know.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] But my parents never ever told me of the horrendous conditions in that camp.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
